  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    ActivatedPowerUpManager
    ActivatedPowerUpManager is responsible to generate, activate and deactivate power-ups.
    AnimatedVisual
    Container for multiple visuals which represent an animated visual.
    Asteroid
    Asteroid is a type of obstacle in the Space-Runner Game, which moves diagonally.
    Coin
    Coin is a SpaceElement that can be collided with and picked up by the SpaceShip to increase the coin count.
    ContentId
    Content ids for content available in the shop.
    DoubleCoinsPowerUp
    DoubleCoinsPowerUp is a power-up which doubles the coin value for a certain time when collected.
    FileResource
    This interface is for all enums which represent a file resource
    FPSTracker
    This class will track the Frames per Second.
    FXMLFile
    Enumeration of the FXML-files that are being used, containing the file path to the FXML.
    FXMLImageProxy
    Image proxy for FXML-Images.
    GameController
    The GameController is responsible for the game logic of the Space-Runner application.
    GameControllerTest  
    GameDataCache
    Stores the achievements of a game to be used in different views (e.g. for game-ended-view).
    GameEndedViewController
    Displays achievements of a game and redirects the user to his/her next desired view.
    GameFile
    This enumeration shows the game files used by the persistence util.
    GameRatioUtil
    Calculates sizes and ratio required in the game ui.
    GameRatioUtilTest  
    GameSound
    Sound files used by the space-runner game
    GameSoundUtil
    Project specific wrapper for the SoundUtil
    GameSoundUtilTest  
    GameViewController
    Visual appearance of the game.
    GameViewPort
    Holds the calculated sizes, according to ratio (from GameRatioUtil.java), for the game.
    HelpViewController
    Displays description of game functionality.
    HorizontalSpeed
    Horizontal speed of elements per second relative to the view.
    ItemType
    Different types of items listed in the shop.
    JsonPersistenceUtil
    Utility tool to persist data (load / save) with Gson-library Implemented with the singleton-pattern
    JsonPersistenceUtilTest  
    MenuViewController
    Visual entry point of program.
    Obstacle
    Obstacle is an abstract class.
    Persistence
    Interface for Persistence (Database / File Storage)
    PlayerProfile
    Data model for the personal profile of the player
    PlayStates
    The different states a SoundClip can be in.
    PowerUp
    PowerUp is a space element that gives the spaceship a special ability when it's collected during a game.
    PowerUpListener
    A PowerUpListener which is implemented by ActivatedPowerUpManager to execute the logic when a power-ups effect is run out after a certain time.
    PowerUpTest
    Tests methods in PowerUp.
    Preset
    In preset several SpaceElements can be stored.
    PresetTest  
    PresetType
    Different types of presets.
    RandomPresetGenerator
    In this class the different presets are created, which are can shown randomly in the game.
    RandomPresetGeneratorTest  
    ResourcesTest
    These tests will find unused resources and FileResource enum entries which don't have an existing file in the resources!
    Rocket
    Rocket is a type of obstacle in the Space-Runner Game, which moves horizontally in a straight line.
    SettingsViewController
    Processes user input and persists the adjustments of the profile.
    ShieldPowerUp
    The ShieldPowerUp is a power-up which gives the spaceship an extra shield.
    ShopContent
    Data model for the content in the shop
    ShopContentCellController
    Shop-view (Shop.fxml) has multiple ShopContentCells.
    ShopContentCellControllerListener
    The ShopContentCellControllerListener is used to depict the updated coin-value in ShopViewController, when a shop content was purchased in ShopContentCellController by pressing the buy-Button.
    ShopViewController
    The ShopViewController is a controller-class, which is responsible for the shop-view (Shop.fxml).
    SoundClip
    SoundClip Object that offers methods related to handling playback.
    SoundClipListener
    With this interface, Objects can listen to a clip and receive events.
    SoundUtil
    SoundUtil to load sound / set volume
    SpaceElement
    SpaceElement is the superclass to all Elements in the game (including SpaceShip, Coin, SpaceWorld and Obstacles) It contains the code for initialization, movement and collision of these Elements.
    SpaceElementTest  
    SpaceRunnerApp
    Responsible to start application, display of user-interfaces and to initialize background sound.
    SpaceShip
    SpaceShip is the SpaceElement that the player controls.
    SpaceShipDirection
    The directions that the SpaceShip can move in.
    SpaceShipTest  
    SpaceWorld
    The background of the game.
    SpaceWorldTest  
    TestDataModel  
    TestDataModelExtended  
    UFO
    UFO is a type of obstacle in the Space-Runner Game, which moves to the left in a wavey motion.
    UFOTest  
    UIVisualElement
    Self made enum with classes.
    VelocityManager
    This is a Manager for the Velocity of the different SpaceElements.
    VelocityManagerTest  
    VelocityNotSetException
    Exception to be thrown if there is no visual set
    VerticalSpeed
    Vertical speed of elements per second relative to the view.
    ViewController
    Defines required methods of a ViewController and stores the achievements of the last played game.
    Visual
    This class is used to specify a visual and load it with the visual manager.
    VisualElement
    Interface to specify which classes can be loaded with the VisualManager
    VisualFile
    Path variables of all image files which are not SCG files.
    VisualManager
    This is a Manager for the Visuals of the different VisualElement's.
    VisualManagerListener
    Implemented this interface to register to Events from VisualManager.
    VisualManagerTest  
    VisualNotSetException
    Exception for case where there is no visual set.
    VisualScaling
    Scaling for visual elements.
    VisualSVGAnimationFiles
    Used to define Animations.
    VisualSVGFile
    Path variables of all images which are SVG files.
    VisualUtil
    Util to load visuals Implemented with the singleton-pattern.
    VisualUtilTest
